   {
      "body" : "Indeed, you can define flags using an enum, but you can't use the enum as parameter when you want to be able to specify multiple flags as it's no longer an enumeration. I believe Qt has a 'typesafe flags' type but that doesn't help us here :) I do think defining the flag values using an enum has a nicer syntax than a list of const XXX.\r\n\r\nAnd I agree with @jgarzik that it's better to have anything that you manipulate bitwise be unsigned. It steers clear of crazy undefined areas of C++, such as overflows flipping the sign bit.\r\n",
      "created_at" : "2012-11-14T06:29:25Z",
